data.content:
Output is `{"name":"Jane","age":30}` as expected. The key piece is:

```csharp
var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
};
```

`JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization. No extra NuGet packages needed — `System.Text.Json` is built into .NET 8.
